Key Match Events: Trezeguet scored a first-half brace, Mohamed Salah scored the third goal in the 56th minute, and Fathi scored Egypt's fourth goal
Post-Match Reflections: Egypt's manager Hossam Hassan praised his team's performance, Trezeguet was the best player on the pitch, and Mohamed Salah was at his devastating best
Miscellaneous Highlights: Botswana will return to international football action in October, Egypt will face Mauritania in a doubleheader, and the gulf in quality between the two sides was too much for Botswana
Others: The match was played on September 10, 2024, and Egypt won 4-0, the match was part of the African Cup of Nations Qualification, Group C, Round 2
